**Iterative Code**

```
class Solution {
public:
    int brokenCalc(int startValue, int target) {
        // In this approach, instead of thinking how
        // to approach from start to target, let's think 
        // how to go from target to start

        /*
        ONE CRUX:

            1. If our target is lesser than start then
               ans will always be the differece
            eg. startValue = 20, target = 5.
            In this example multiplying will not do anything
            so, ans = (startValue - target) = 20 - 5 = 15;

            2. Otherwise, we'll check if target is odd/even

                -> for even numbers, we can directly divide by 2
                -> for odd numbers, we'll increase the target by 1
                   just to divide by 2 in the next step

        */
        int cnt = 0;

        while(target > startValue)
        {
            if(target&1)
                target++;
            else
                target/=2;

            cnt++;
        }

        return cnt + startValue - target;
    }
};
```

