**Approach:**
* Here, we do opposite operations we reduce targetvalue until it is lesser than startvalue
* For this we apply just 2 opposite operations....
i) If target is odd, add 1 to it
ii) If target is even, divide it by 2
* increment count by 1 for each operation and return it.
* **TC-O(LogN), SC- O(1)**

**Code:**
```
class Solution {
public:
    int brokenCalc(int startValue, int target) 
    {
        //variable for counting no. of operations
        int cnt=0;

        while(startValue < target)
        {
            if(target%2) // odd (t%2==1 for odd)
            {
                target++;
            }

            else //even (t%2==0 for even)
            {
                target /= 2;
            }

            //increment count
            cnt++;
        }
        return cnt + (startValue - target);

    }
};
```

