According to the question, we can perform two types of operations:
1] X=X*2;
2]X=X-1;

It can be easily observed that when  X>Y  ito reach Y in minimum number of steps, we should 
only use the second operation.But  when Y>X  we don't get any clear idea as such about how to proceed.(And as   1<=X,Y<=1e9  brute force approach would lead to TLE.)

If you observe both the give operations are in terms of X;
Now if consider equivalent operations in terms of Y(and try to X from Y), it would as follows:
1] Y=Y/2;
2]Y=Y+1;

We can say that this set of Operations (i.e the one w.r.t Y)  are more convinient as,
the 1st operation can only be applied if Y is even.Similarly if Y is odd operation 1 cannot be performed hence only allowed operation remain operation 2.

So From this we can say that-->
if(Y is odd) Y=Y+1;
else Y=Y/2;

And we repeat the above until Y becomes X.

