# Basic Idea

1. I am Y, and I want to become X.
    - Question arises why not start from X and go to Y? Well,  if you start from X, you can't say for sure that is X*2 more optimal or X-1 will give a better solution. Why so? Because there is no criteria for you to judge.  This will become more clear, when you read below.

2. If I am divisible by 2, I can simply reduce myself to half my number in one step.
    - Question arises why did I not increment myself by 1, how is dividing by 2  an optimal step? Well, listen. I want to reach X in the least possible steps,

        My Goal : Y → X 

        Case 1 : Y → Y/2 ————→ X . Say steps taken are C_1
        Case 2 : Y → Y+1 → Y+1 → Y/2 ——→ X. Steps taken will be C_1 + 2
        { If a number is  not divisible by  2 you can't divide it by 2, that is against the rules of the question | 

        *To sum up every time you increment by 1, you will take 2 more steps to reach X. So Y/2 is surely the optimal solution.*

3. If I am not divisible by 2, the only option I have is to increment myself by 1.


